---
description: React + TypeScript rules for this repo
globs: ["**/*.{ts,tsx}"]
---

## Components & hooks

- Use **function components** and React hooks (repo uses React 18).
- Mark client components with `"use client";` when using hooks like `useState`, `useEffect`, or `useRouter`.
- For App Router pages, keep server components minimal; pass `searchParams` from `page.tsx` into client components when needed (see `app/sign-in/page.tsx`).

## Styling (MUI)

- Prefer **MUI components** and the `sx` prop for styling.
- Theme token builders exist:
  - `app/getLPTheme.tsx`
  - `app/getSignUpInTheme.tsx`
  - `app/checkout/getCheckoutTheme.tsx`

## Data fetching (React Query)

- Prefer React Query for server data:
  - define typed hooks in `app/services/*` using `useQuery`/`useMutation`.
- Keep query keys stable and explicit (examples in `app/services/DialogService.tsx`).

## HTTP (axios)

- Use `apiInstance` (base `/api`) for backend endpoints and `instance` (base `/`) for `/login`.
- Auth is cookie-based (`withCredentials: true`).
- Be aware of the global response interceptor in `app/services/ApiInstance.tsx`:
  - it can unwrap `data.body`
  - it can redirect to `/sign-in?next=...` if an HTML sign-in page is returned

## Dates (dayjs)

- `dayjs` is used in multiple components (e.g. trip forms and app bar). Prefer `dayjs` for user-facing date handling where already used.
- Date formatting helpers also exist in `app/utils/dateFormatters.ts`.

